'''Kubotsu Ōji''' ('''くぼつおうじ''') is the first of the {{ill|Kumano Gongen|ja|熊野権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Gongen|qq=}}'s {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|ja|熊野九十九王子|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} shrines. It was located near the {{ill|Hachikenya Boat Dock|ja|八軒家船着場|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachikenya Boat Dock|qq=}} in the {{ill|Tenmabashi|ja|天満橋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmabashi|qq=}} area of {{ill|Chūō-ku, Osaka|ja|中央区 (大阪市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chūō-ku, Osaka|qq=}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka City|qq=}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Prefecture|qq=}}. Today, the site is marked by the {{ill|Ikasuri Shrine|ja|坐摩神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikasuri Shrine|qq=}} {{nihongo|Temporary Shrine|行宮}}.
Later, Kubotsu Ōji was enshrined as {{ill|Kumano Shrine|ja|熊野神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Shrine|qq=}} near the western gate of {{ill|Shitennō-ji|ja|四天王寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitennō-ji|qq=}}. On February 10, {{ill|1915|ja|1915th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1915|qq=}} (Taishō 4), it was relocated to {{ill|Horikoshi Shrine|ja|堀越神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikoshi Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Horikoshi Town|ja|堀越町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikoshi Town|qq=}}, {{ill|Tennoji-ku, Osaka|ja|天王寺区|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tennoji-ku, Osaka|qq=}}, where it is now a subordinate shrine known as "Kumano Daiichi Ōji Shrine" (熊野第一王子社).
The {{ill|Ikasuri Shrine|ja|坐摩神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikasuri Shrine|qq=}} originally stood at this location but was moved to {{ill|Kyūtarō-machi, Osaka|ja|久太郎町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyūtarō-machi, Osaka|qq=}} in Chūō-ku during the construction of {{ill|Osaka Castle|ja|大阪城|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Castle|qq=}}. Many retired emperors (*jōkō*) who undertook the {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野御幸|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Pilgrimage|qq=}} also visited this site.
