九王子 (日高町)#小中王子|小中王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[九十九王子 (日高町)#比井王子|比井王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[九十九王子 (日高町)#松原王子|松原王子]] --><!--Kubotsu Ōji--><!--Kubotsu Ōji--> [[Category:Buildings in Chuo-ku, Osaka]] [[Category:History of Chuo-ku, Osaka]] <!--jawiki derived wikidata interwikis--> [[Category:pages without english wikidata name]] [[sn:Kubotsu Ōji Shrine]][[en:Kubotsu Ōji]]

{{Infobox religious building|prefecture={{ill|Osaka|qid=Q35765}}}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11597673]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:41, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Kubotsu Ōji''' ('''くぼつおうじ''') is the first of the {{ill|Kumano Gongen|ja|熊野権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Gongen|qq=}}'s {{ill|Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|ja|熊野九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 九十九王子|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3200280}} shrines. It was located near the {{ill|Hachikenya Boat Dock|ja|八軒家船着場|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachikenya Boat Dock|qq=}} in the {{ill|Tenmabashi|ja|天満橋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmabashi|qq=|1=Tenma Bridge|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q18215296}} area of [[:en:Chūō-ku, Osaka|Chūō-ku, Osaka]], [[:en:Osaka|Osaka City]], [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]]. Today, the site is marked by the [[:en:Ikasuri Shrine|Ikasuri Shrine]] {{nihongo|Temporary Shrine|行宮}}.
Later, Kubotsu Ōji was enshrined as [[:en:Kumano shrine|Kumano Shrine]] near the western gate of [[:en:Shitennō-ji|Shitennō-ji]]. On February 10, [[:en:1915|1915]] (Taishō 4), it was relocated to {{ill|Horikoshi Shrine|ja|堀越神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikoshi Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Horikoshi Town|ja|堀越町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikoshi Town|qq=|1=Horikoshi Town|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q18989850}}, [[:en:Tennōji-ku, Osaka|Tennoji-ku, Osaka]], where it is now a subordinate shrine known as "Kumano Daiichi Ōji Shrine" (熊野第一王子社).
The [[:en:Ikasuri Shrine|Ikasuri Shrine]] originally stood at this location but was moved to {{ill|Kyūtarō-machi, Osaka|ja|久太郎町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyūtarō-machi, Osaka|qq=|1=Kyūtarō-machi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q60996434}} in Chūō-ku during the construction of {{ill|Osaka Castle|ja|大阪城|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Castle|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大坂城|1=Osaka Castle|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q321242}}. Many retired emperors (*jōkō*) who undertook the {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野御幸|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Pilgrimage|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135506327}} also visited this site.
